ZH: 老师鼓励学生多提问。
EN: The teacher encourages students to ask questions.

ZH: 对于难懂的问题，可以随时提问。
EN: You can ask questions anytime for difficult problems.

ZH: 我们鼓励员工提问，以便更好地理解工作内容。
EN: We encourage employees to ask questions in order to better understand the job.

ZH: 学生们应该积极提问，不要担心出错。
EN: Students should ask questions actively without worrying about making mistakes.

ZH: 别害羞，提问不会让你丢脸。
EN: Don't be shy, asking questions will not make you lose face.

ZH: 在课堂上，同学们应该提问，不要怕打扰。
EN: In class, students should ask questions without being afraid of disturbing others.

ZH: 他总是喜欢提问，为了弄清楚每个细节。
EN: He always likes to ask questions in order to understand every detail.

ZH: 在团队会议上，大家都鼓励提问。
EN: In team meetings, everyone encourages asking questions.

ZH: 学习时，提问是获取知识的有效方式。
EN: Asking questions is an effective way to gain knowledge while studying.

ZH: 请随时提问，我们很乐意帮助你解决问题。
EN: Please feel free to ask questions, we are happy to help you solve problems.

ZH: 如果你不明白，请举手提问。
EN: Raise your hand to ask a question if you don't understand.

ZH: 在学习过程中，要勇于提问。
EN: Be brave to ask questions during the learning process.

ZH: 他准备了一些问题，明天课堂上会提问老师。
EN: He prepared some questions and will ask the teacher in class tomorrow.

ZH: 不要怕提问，只有问过的人才会懂。
EN: Don't be afraid to ask questions, only those who ask will understand.

ZH: 上课时，同学们都积极提问，课程变得更加生动。
EN: During class, students are actively asking questions, making the lessons more engaging.

ZH: 在商务会议上，应该有时间安排提问环节。
EN: There should be time allocated for asking questions during business meetings.

ZH: 请补充提问和回答的内容，以便更好地理解这个问题。
EN: Please provide additional questions and answers to better understand the problem.

ZH: 做任何决定前，应该多提问，避免遗漏重要细节。
EN: Before making any decision, ask more questions to avoid missing important details.

ZH: 听众们纷纷提问，演讲者耐心回答他们的问题。
EN: The audience asked questions one after another, and the speaker patiently answered their questions.
